      "role": "user",
      "content": "The goblin analogy is a bit confusing. I need to focus on the technical side. You mentioned the state_machine_v2 had an \"unexpected state\" in the fatal error. Given the deadlock and the connection timeout, what specifically could be causing the state machine to transition into an invalid state? Is it a consequence of the lock failure, or something else?",
